    <skos:related rdf:resource="http://purl.org/heritagedata/schemes/eh_tbm/concepts/98036"/>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Soft, often white, but may be transparent. Dolomite can be found on its own, but may also occur as a replacement mineral found in some rocks, particularly limestone, formed after action by magnesium-rich fluids.</skos:scopeNote>
